zk is madetory for kafka, without zk, kafka wont work.
Few basic operations:

navigate to base directory: cd ~/Applications/kafka_2.10-0.10.0.1/

start zookeeper:
	./bin/zookeeper-server-start.sh ./config/zookeeper.properties

start kafka server:
	bin/kafka-server-start.sh ./config/server.properties

list all kafka topics:
	./bin/kafka-topics.sh --zookeeper localhost:2181 --list

create kafka topic:
	./bin/kafka-topics.sh --zookeeper localhost:2181 --create --topic test2 --replication-factor 1 --partition 3

kafka console consumer: 
	./bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh --zookeeper localhost:2181 --topic test.topic --from-beginning

kafka console producer:
	./bin/kafka-console-producer.sh --broker-list localhost:9092 --topic test.topic

// zk specific
	connect to zk shell:
		./bin/zookeeper-shell.sh localhost:2181
	type commands here which you want to see, you can also have separate zk and then call zkCli.sh to login to zk 
	list broker-ids: 
		ls /brokers/ids
	list broker topics:
		ls /brokers/topics
	remove broker from zk (znodes-emphemeral nodes)
		rmr /broker/ids/0
		rmr /test
	Ephemeral znodes (flag: e) will be automatically deleted when a session expires or when the client disconnects.
		create z-nodes:
			Syntax: create [options] /path /data
			eg: create -e /my/path "mydata"
	Sequential znodes guaranty that the znode path will be unique.
		create sequential nodes:
			Syntax: create [options] /path /data
			eg: create -s /my/path "mydata"
	
 